      "content": "The FOB agreement itself doesn't change the fundamental liability in cases of piracy or theft at sea; because the risk has transferred to you, you are responsible for the loss. If the goods are hijacked or stolen while in transit, you must rely on the cargo insurance you purchased to cover the loss. Your insurance policy, not the FOB contract, will dictate whether and how you are reimbursed for such an unfortunate incident. It's essential to have a robust policy that covers perils like piracy.",
